# Marketing article authoring

When editing or creating articles under `web/src/data/marketing/articleContent.ts`, follow these rules so site content and **Copy for X** stay consistent.

## Em dash (required)

1. **Never use the em dash character `—`** (U+2014) in titles, excerpts, descriptions, bios, or markdown body.
2. Prefer a **comma** for clause breaks (`machine money, pay-per-call APIs`).
3. Prefer a **colon** for label → value (`Package: Purpose`, table cells).
4. `articleXCopy` normalizes leftover em dashes as a safety net, but source content must still be clean.

## Structure

1. Keep `excerpt` as the short dek (1–2 sentences) shown under the title and used in X copy.
2. Use `##` for section headings and `###` for subheadings.
3. Prefer short paragraphs (1–3 sentences). Long walls of text paste poorly on mobile X.
4. Use `-` / `1.` lists and `> [!NOTE]` callouts where they help scanning.

## X Articles paste behavior

**Copy for X** writes `text/html` + `text/plain`. Only emit tags X auto-formats on paste.

| Paste-supported | Remapped in copy | Manual in X Insert |
| --- | --- | --- |
| h2 / h3 heading | table → bullet list | Underline |
| body paragraph | code fence → quote ("Code") | Native divider |
| bold, italic, strike | inline `code` → bold | Native code block |
| links (absolutized) | `---` → `· · ·` | LaTeX |
| quote / callout | relative `/path` → `https://www.syraa.fun/path` | Native table |
| bullet / numbered list | | Images (upload) |

Never paste `<table>`, `<pre>`, `<h1>`, or `<hr>` into X. Title uses bold lead text (X title field owns h1).

## Checklist for new articles

- [ ] No `—` anywhere in the article object
- [ ] Title, description, excerpt filled
- [ ] Cover image path under `/images/articles/`
- [ ] Tags / category set
- [ ] Content uses headings + short paragraphs
- [ ] Run `npx vitest run src/lib/marketing/articleXCopy.test.ts` after content edits
